The new album of the David Band led by Yaga Pastor has been launched at the Ogba area of Lagos recently. Speaking at the occasion, the artiste, Mr. David Ogbantu, aka. Yaga Pastor, said, he decided to go into gospel music in order to satisfy his numerous fans. The new album, titled ‘Double Anointing’, has six tracks, ‘Double Anointing’, ‘Kata War Inna Devils Kingdom’, ‘Why Do You Run Away’, ‘Good Morning Sir’, ‘Permanent Solution’ and ‘Say It You Love Me’. -Advertisement- The free flowing music of the David Band, a brand of Gospel music with a touch of reggae and pop influence, was dedicated to the son of God, Jesus Christ. Yaga Pastor is a product of Tabansi Records, which made their mark in 70s and 80s, a label that produced artistes like the late Majek Fashek, Andy Showman, Isaac Black, etc. ‘Double Anointing’ album produced at Trinity Records has as hit track ‘Kata War’ is also the second by Yaga Pastor, whose debut was released a decade ago. The album, although launched recently, has already been receiving attention by the air wave from some radio stations in Lagos. According to some of his fans, this gospel album is a clear diversion of his usual music with a creativity of a new brand of rhythm, called Yaga System.